1515–1558","1561–1586":"1561–1586","1558":"1558","1557":"1557","1523":"1523","1610":"1610","1544":"1544","1586":"1586","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1561":"1561","1570":"1570","1515":"1515","Berga,Kronoberg,Sweden":"Berga, Kronoberg, Sweden","Skälboö, Östergötland, Sverige":"Skälboö, Östergötland, Sweden","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Chardstock, Dorset, , England":"Chardstock, Dorset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Adeleid","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘sort, kind’.  See also  <b>Adelaide</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702079,"age":5,"year":"1520","julianDay":2276228,"title":"The Stockholm Bloodbath","description":"A mass execution of Swedish nobles by Danish king Christian II is known as the Stockholm Bloodbath. Christian II invaded Sweden in 1519 and took hold of Stockholm in September 1520. Over 80 nobles were executed for heresy on November 8 and 9. The outrage from the executions led to the Swedish removal of support of the Kalmar Union.","url":"https://www.britannica.com/event/Stockholm-Bloodbath","urlTitle":"Britannica - Stockholm Bloodbath","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702080,"age":8,"year":"1523","julianDay":2277324,"title":"Swedish War of Liberation","description":"The Swedish War of Liberation was a civil war led by nobleman Gustav Vasa. As Christian II heard of the rebellion, he confronted Vasa's men, who won the battle at Brunbacks Ferry. Christian II was defeated by the Swedes in Stockholm and a truce was agreed upon. Vasa was given as a hostage as a show of good faith until the treaty was signed. The Danish King did not keep his word and Vasa was held as a prisoner for two years until his escape. A bounty was placed on Vasa's head. Vasa worked to inspire many to join his cause and lived under disguise until the Danes surrendered in 1525.","url":"https://www.sweden.org.za/swedish-monarchy-gustav-vasa.html","urlTitle":"Sweden.org - Swedish Monarchy Gustav Vasa","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702085,"age":25,"year":"1540","julianDay":2283533,"title":"First Full Swedish Translation of the Bible","description":"The first full Swedish translation of the Bible, known as the Gustav Bible, was completed by Olaus Petri and Laurentius Andreae and published in 1540.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702086,"age":29,"year":"1544","julianDay":2284994,"title":"Sweden Becomes Lutheran Nation","description":"Sweden officially declared itself a Lutheran nation in 1544.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357054,"age":55,"year":"1570","julianDay":2294491,"description":"Peace of Stettin concluded. Denmark recognized independence of Sweden. Sweden gave up claim to Norway.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Adeleid Wackerbarth was born in 1515, in Berga, Kronoberg, Sweden. She married Johan Claesson Von Zijlen Neuendorff in 1557, in Skälboö, Östergötland, Sweden. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1610, at the age of 95."},"et":{"1515–1610":"1515–1610","1515–1558":"1515–1558","1561–1586":"1561–1586","1558":"1558","1557":"1557","1523":"1523","1610":"1610","1544":"1544","1586":"1586","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1561":"1561","1570":"1570","1515":"1515","Berga,Kronoberg,Sweden":"Berga, Kronoberg, Rootsi","Skälboö, Östergötland, Sverige":"Skälboö, Östergötland, Rootsi","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chardstock, Dorset, , England":"Chardstock, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1515–1610":"1515–1610","1515–1558":"1515–1558","1561–1586":"1561–1586","1558":"1558","1557":"1557","1523":"1523","1610":"1610","1544":"1544","1586":"1586","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1561":"1561","1570":"1570","1515":"1515","Berga,Kronoberg,Sweden":"Berga, Kronoberg, Ruotsi","Skälboö, Östergötland, Sverige":"Skälboö, Östergötland, Ruotsi","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chardstock, Dorset, , E